The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 August is 60,956 (7,025.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 August, there were 2,512 new confirmed cases (289.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 July, there were 2,203 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 14% (309 extra cases).
